            <dt>
                <a href="#accordion2" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="accordion2" class="accordion-title accordionTitle js-accordionTrigger">
                    Bees / Hornets / Yellow Jackets
                </a>
            </dt>
            <dd class="accordion-content accordionItem is-collapsed" id="accordion2" aria-hidden="true">
                <p>Upland Pest Control encourages environmental stewardship and recommends live bee hive removal 
                whenever possible.  This service can be involved and time consuming Upland Pest Control works with 
                local bee keepers who practice safe, low stress removal for the bees in order to keep the colony together.</p>

                <p>My number one goal is resident safety.  Hives or nests causing concern can be treated and eliminated.  
                Removal is priced separately according to the complexity of the removal process. If a hive is not 
                removed, it could draw bees or other pests back or can begin to give off an odor and ooze down the walls.  </p>

                <p>
                    For more information about Bees / Hornets / Yellow Jackets visit: <br />
                    <a href="http://extension.colostate.edu/docs/pubs/insect/05525.pdf" target="_blank">Colorado State Univ - Wasps & Bees</a><br />
                    <a href="http://extension.colostate.edu/docs/pubs/insect/05611.pdf" target="_blank">Colorado State Univ - European Paper Wasp</a><br />
                </p>
            </dd>
            <dt>
                <a href="#accordion3" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="accordion3" class="accordion-title accordionTitle js-accordionTrigger">
                    Birds / Pigeons
                </a>
            </dt>
            <dd class="accordion-content accordionItem is-collapsed" id="accordion3" aria-hidden="true">
                <p>Birds control is very important not only for the unsightly things they do to your property, but they 
                also carry and spread diseases. It is important to take a proactive stance when dealing with birds. Not 
                only can this save you time in the future but also money. Here are some of the common reasons why proper 
                bird control is necessary: property damage, health hazards, costly cleanup, unsightly image as well as parasites.  
                Upland Pest Control offers multiple options when dealing with nuisance birds.</p>

                <p>
                    For more information about Birds / Pigeons visit: <br />
                    <a href="http://extension.colostate.edu/docs/pubs/natres/06516.pdf" target="_blank">Colorado State Univ - Preventing Woodpecker Damage</a><br />
                </p>
            </dd>
