            <dt>
                <a href="#accordion5" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="accordion5" class="accordion-title accordionTitle js-accordionTrigger">
                    Fleas / Flies
                </a>
            </dt>
            <dd class="accordion-content accordionItem is-collapsed" id="accordion5" aria-hidden="true">
                <p>Upland Pest Control has developed an effective two-step flea control method to eliminate fleas from 
                your home.  To attain the best results, proper home preparation by the homeowner is required before each treatment. 
                Before your flea treatment, I’ll provide you with a list of preparation you will need to take.  In the first 
                step I will treat the inside and outside of your home twice within 10 to 14 days. I will pay close attention to 
                pet areas where the highest concentration of flea eggs and larvae will be located.</p>

                <p>After the initial treatment, the homeowner will need to vacuum at least three (3) times a week to pick up eggs 
                and larvae that reproduce during the time it takes your animals’ flea treatment to be effective. Effective flea control 
                requires treating your animals as well.</p>

                <p>
                    For more information about Fleas / Flies visit: <br />
                    <a href="http://www.ipm.ucdavis.edu/PDF/PESTNOTES/pnflies.pdf" target="_blank">UC Davis - Flies</a><br />
                    <a href="http://extension.colostate.edu/docs/pubs/insect/05600.pdf" target="_blank">Colorado State Univ - Fleas and Plague</a><br />
                </p>
            </dd>
            <dt>
                <a href="#accordion6" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="accordion6" class="accordion-title accordionTitle js-accordionTrigger">
                    Gophers
                </a>
            </dt>
            <dd class="accordion-content accordionItem is-collapsed" id="accordion6" aria-hidden="true">
                <p>Gophers eat your plants and dig invisible tunnels underground damaging your landscape and possibly underground utilities.  
                They also leave fan-shaped mounds in your yards and landscaped areas.  They can be very hard to combat.  Once I have assessed 
                the degree of infestation I will apply the appropriate control measures to get rid of the gophers on your property. Treatments 
                are sold by application based on the size of the infested area.</p>

                <p>
                    For more information about Gophers visit: <br />
                    <a href="http://extension.colostate.edu/docs/pubs/natres/06515.pdf" target="_blank">Colorado State Univ - Managing Pocket Gophers</a><br />
                </p>
            </dd>
            <dt>
                <a href="#accordion7" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="accordion7" class="accordion-title accordionTitle js-accordionTrigger">
                    Mosquitoes
                </a>
            </dt>
            <dd class="accordion-content accordionItem is-collapsed" id="accordion7" aria-hidden="true">
                <p>As part of an integrated pest management approach to your problem I will begin with and inspection of the property for 
                where mosquito's most likely harborage and their entry points into the interior of the home. Most mosquitoes rest during the 
                day in secluded and shady areas such as, tall grasses, in shrubs, trees, arbors and building eaves.  My approach to mosquito 
                control includes treating or removing breeding sites as well as treating harborage locations where biting adults hide.</p>

                <p>
                    For more information about Mosquitoes visit: <br />
                    <a href="http://www.ipm.ucdavis.edu/PDF/PESTNOTES/pnmosquitoes.pdf" target="_blank">UC Davis - Mosquitoes</a><br />
                </p>
            </dd>
            <dt>
                <a href="#accordion8" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="accordion8" class="accordion-title accordionTitle js-accordionTrigger">
                    Pantry Pests
                </a>
            </dt>
            <dd class="accordion-content accordionItem is-collapsed" id="accordion8" aria-hidden="true">
                <p>My pantry pest control will rid your cupboards of pests.  Here’s what our specialized service involves:  My treatment 
                for pantry pests is very thorough and effective and consist of a three phase approach: Inspect, Remove and Treat.  I’ll perform 
                a thorough inspection to determine the extent of the infestation.  Remove pests and debris from all accessible areas and treat 
                throughout the home concentrating on the most infested areas. Treatment may include topical sprays and pheromone traps.  
                Heavy infestations may require another treatment.  Pantry pest treatments are sold by application.</p>

                <p>
                    For more information about Pantry Pests visit: <br />
                    <a href="http://www.ipm.ucdavis.edu/PDF/PESTNOTES/pnpantrypests.pdf" target="_blank">UC Davis - Pantry Pests</a><br />
                </p>
            </dd>
            <dt>
                <a href="#accordion9" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="accordion9" class="accordion-title accordionTitle js-accordionTrigger">
                    Prarie Dogs
                </a>
            </dt>
            <dd class="accordion-content accordionItem is-collapsed" id="accordion9" aria-hidden="true">
                <p>Colorado Springs is the home of the black-tailed and Gunnison prairie dogs.  Both species of prairie dogs are host to fleas 
                which make them susceptible to bubonic plague. All forms of plague can be transmitted to humans.  Although prairie dogs can present 
                a public health concern most control programs are undertaken because of the damage these rodents do to vegetation and rangeland.  
                Upland Pest Control offers effective extermination services both in rangeland areas and in and around structures.  Ask about our 
                discounts for large rangeland infestations.</p>

                <p>
                    For more information about Prarie Dogs visit: <br />
                    <a href="http://extension.colostate.edu/docs/pubs/natres/06506.pdf" target="_blank">Colorado State Univ - Managing Prarie Dogs</a><br />
                </p>
            </dd>
            <dt>
                <a href="#accordion10" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="accordion10" class="accordion-title accordionTitle js-accordionTrigger">
                    Raccoons
                </a>
            </dt>
            <dd class="accordion-content accordionItem is-collapsed" id="accordion10" aria-hidden="true">
                <p>The raccoon or the “masked bandit” is native to North America. Raccoons will create homes in the wild but they also look for warm 
                safe places, commonly getting in to attics, out buildings and inside of chimneys. Because of this, people should always have a chimney 
                cap installed. Raccoons carry diseases which include rabies, canine distemper, and raccoon roundworm.  Upland Pest Control will whenever 
                possible release these animals back to the wild in accordance with Colorado laws.</p>

                <p>
                    For more information about Raccoons visit: <br />
                    <a href="http://www.ipm.ucdavis.edu/PDF/PESTNOTES/pnraccoons.pdf" target="_blank">UC Davis - Raccoons</a><br />
                    <a href="http://extension.entm.purdue.edu/publications/ADM-17.pdf" target="_blank">Purdue Univ - Animal Damage Management</a><br />
                </p>
            </dd>
            <dt>
                <a href="#accordion11" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="accordion11" class="accordion-title accordionTitle js-accordionTrigger">
                    Rats / Mice
                </a>
            </dt>
            <dd class="accordion-content accordionItem is-collapsed" id="accordion11" aria-hidden="true">
                <p>Upland Pest Control has developed an effective three-step approach to controlling rodents in and around your home.  First Survey of your 
                property, evaluate the situation for rodent activity and set up exterior bait stations.  Second inspect the interior of the home for damage 
                (photos can be taken and a report is provided at the request of the home owner).  Recommend control and remedial actions which may include 
                trapping, baiting, cleanup, sanitation and exclusion services.  </p>

                <p>
                    For more information about Rats / Mice visit: <br />
                    <a href="http://extension.colostate.edu/docs/pubs/natres/06507.pdf" target="_blank">Colorado State Univ - Voles in Colorado</a><br />
                </p>
            </dd>
            <dt>
                <a href="#accordion12" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="accordion12" class="accordion-title accordionTitle js-accordionTrigger">
                    Skunks
                </a>
            </dt>
            <dd class="accordion-content accordionItem is-collapsed" id="accordion12" aria-hidden="true">
                <p>Skunks are mostly nocturnal, and look at night eating a variety of different foods. Skunks often live under homes, patios, decks, and sheds. 
                Skunks do not fully hibernate, but activity is very low during the winter. Skunks can carry Rabies, Distemper, and Leptospirosis.  Colorado State 
                law does not allow the relocation of skunks.  Upland Pest Control follows American Veterinary Medical Association guidelines for humane treatment 
                of animals.</p>

