            <dt>
                <a href="#accordion15" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="accordion15" class="accordion-title accordionTitle js-accordionTrigger">
                    Squirrels
                </a>
            </dt>
            <dd class="accordion-content accordionItem is-collapsed" id="accordion15" aria-hidden="true">
                <p>Upland Pest Control offers control strategies for both tree and rock squirrels.  Tree squirrels usually nest in trees. However squirrels often invade 
                a home, and will live the attic, eaves, soffits, above a ceiling, or in the walls. Squirrels can cause a lot of damage. They are rodents, and chew on 
                electrical wires, wood, and anything else they can find.</p>

                <p>Rock Squirrels, with their long, bushy tails, look very much like tree squirrels, but seldom climb trees. As their name implies they are most commonly 
                found in rocky environments.  However, they’ll happily exploit man-made structures such as outbuildings.  The burrows often extend under sidewalks, dwellings, 
                and outbuildings where they can weaken structural integrity.</p>

                <p>Rock squirrels are also associated with transmission of bubonic plague to humans, but both squirrels can spread various zoonotic diseases.  
                In addition both can cause costly damage to vehicle electrical systems where they gnaw on wires.</p>

                <p>
                    For more information about Squirrels visit: <br />
                    <a href="https://ag.arizona.edu/yavapai/anr/hort/byg/archive/rocksquirrels2010.html" target="_blank">Arizona Univ - Rock Squirrels</a><br />
                    <a href="http://extension.colostate.edu/docs/pubs/natres/06505.pdf" target="_blank">Colorado State Univ - Managing Ground Squirrels</a><br />
